We're off to quite a start, yes. When we "extrapolate from the relativity intensities from the particular cells", we may have left the scientific world and entered the philosophical world. When we "extrapolate", dictionary.com tells us that we;


"infer (an unknown) from something that is known; conjecture." 




 and a conjecture is;



the formation or expression of an opinion or theory without sufficient evidence for proof. 



 I'm now slightly less confused about why I've never seen this discussed before.
